Sentencas: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of composite cathodes, formed from a mixture of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) and Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) nanofibers, is reported.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 co-electrospun nanofiber cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrodes are obtained by simultaneous electrospinning of the two precursor solutions, using apparatus equipped with two spinnerets working in parallel.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 co-electrospun nanofiber cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results of electrochemical testing carried out through electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) are presented and discussed.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 co-electrospun nanofiber cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results suggest that the electrochemical reaction takes place in an electrode region close to the electrode/current collector interface and that the oxygen ions then flow along the ionic conducting path of the GDC fibers.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 co-electrospun nanofiber cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 650 degrees C, the polarization resistance is R-p = 5.6 U cm(-2), in line with literature values reported for other IT-SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Synthesis and electrochemical characterization of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 co-electrospun nanofiber cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
